    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"SA Housing Market: Interactive Price Trends\"\ndescription: \"Exploring residential property price trends across South African metros using R and interactive Plotly charts.\"\ndate: 2025-02-20\ncategories: [R, Plotly, Interactive, Real Estate, South Africa]\nimage: thumbnail.png\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis post explores simulated residential property price indices across four\nmajor South African metros. The charts here are **fully interactive** — hover\nto see values, click the legend to toggle metros, and zoom in on any period.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(plotly)\nlibrary(scales)\n```\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Data\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nset.seed(7)\n\nmetros <- c(\"Johannesburg\", \"Cape Town\", \"Durban\", \"Pretoria\")\nquarters <- seq(as.Date(\"2015-01-01\"), as.Date(\"2024-10-01\"), by = \"quarter\")\n\n# Simulate price index (base = 100 at start) with different growth paths\ndf <- expand_grid(metro = metros, date = quarters) |>\n  arrange(metro, date) |>\n  group_by(metro) |>\n  mutate(\n    base_growth = case_when(\n      metro == \"Cape Town\"     ~ 0.025,\n      metro == \"Johannesburg\"  ~ 0.015,\n      metro == \"Pretoria\"      ~ 0.018,\n      metro == \"Durban\"        ~ 0.010\n    ),\n    noise       = cumsum(rnorm(n(), 0, 0.8)),\n    index       = 100 * cumprod(1 + base_growth / 4 + rnorm(n(), 0, 0.005))\n  ) |>\n  ungroup()\n```\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Interactive Price Index Chart\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot_ly(\n  df,\n  x     = ~date,\n  y     = ~round(index, 1),\n  color = ~metro,\n  type  = \"scatter\",\n  mode  = \"lines\",\n  hovertemplate = \"<b>%{fullData.name}</b><br>%{x|%b %Y}<br>Index: %{y}<extra></extra>\"\n) |>\n  layout(\n    title   = list(text = \"SA Residential Property Price Index (Base = 100, Q1 2015)\"),\n    xaxis   = list(title = \"\"),\n    yaxis   = list(title = \"Price Index\"),\n    legend  = list(title = list(text = \"Metro\")),\n    hovermode = \"x unified\"\n  )\n```\n\n::: {#fig-interactive .cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-402c69fdf9a4f1c553b0\" style=\"width:100%;height:464px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-402c69fdf9a4f1c553b0\">{\"x\":{\"visdat\":{\"13d818cb7885\":[\"function () \",\"plotlyVisDat\"]},\"cur_data\":\"13d818cb7885\",\"attrs\":{\"13d818cb7885\":{\"x\":{},\"y\":{},\"mode\":\"lines\",\"hovertemplate\":\"<b>%{fullData.name}<\\/b><br>%{x|%b %Y}<br>Index: %{y}<extra><\\/extra>\",\"color\":{},\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"type\":\"scatter\"}},\"layout\":{\"margin\":{\"b\":40,\"l\":60,\"t\":25,\"r\":10},\"title\":{\"text\":\"SA Residential Property Price Index (Base = 100, Q1 2015)\"},\"xaxis\":{\"domain\":[0,1],\"automargin\":true,\"title\":\"\"},\"yaxis\":{\"domain\":[0,1],\"automargin\":true,\"title\":\"Price Index\"},\"legend\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Metro\"}},\"hovermode\":\"x unified\",\"showlegend\":true},\"source\":\"A\",\"config\":{\"modeBarButtonsToAdd\":[\"hoverclosest\",\"hovercompare\"],\"showSendToCloud\":false},\"data\":[{\"x\":[\"2015-01-01\",\"2015-04-01\",\"2015-07-01\",\"2015-10-01\",\"2016-01-01\",\"2016-04-01\",\"2016-07-01\",\"2016-10-01\",\"2017-01-01\",\"2017-04-01\",\"2017-07-01\",\"2017-10-01\",\"2018-01-01\",\"2018-04-01\",\"2018-07-01\",\"2018-10-01\",\"2019-01-01\",\"2019-04-01\",\"2019-07-01\",\"2019-10-01\",\"2020-01-01\",\"2020-04-01\",\"2020-07-01\",\"2020-10-01\",\"2021-01-01\",\"2021-04-01\",\"2021-07-01\",\"2021-10-01\",\"2022-01-01\",\"2022-04-01\",\"2022-07-01\",\"2022-10-01\",\"2023-01-01\",\"2023-04-01\",\"2023-07-01\",\"2023-10-01\",\"2024-01-01\",\"2024-04-01\",\"2024-07-01\",\"2024-10-01\"],\"y\":[100.8,101.5,102.09999999999999,103.09999999999999,104.3,104.8,105.59999999999999,106.59999999999999,107.5,107.09999999999999,106.5,107.5,108.8,108.7,109.8,110.59999999999999,111.7,113.099999999